### 2.8 Example Page Structure

```typescript
// src/pages/users/index.tsx — Users List Page
export default function UsersPage() {
  const [filters, setFilters] = useState<UserFilters>({ page: 1, status: "all", search: "" });
  const { data, isLoading } = useUsers(filters);
  const updateStatus = useUpdateUserStatus();

  return (
    <div className="space-y-6">
      {/* Page Header */}
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
        <div>
          <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-text font-urbanist">User Management</h1>
          <p className="text-text-secondary text-sm">Manage registered users and approvals</p>
        </div>
        <Badge variant="outline">{data?.total || 0} users</Badge>
      </div>

      {/* Filters Bar */}
      <div className="flex gap-3">
        <SearchInput value={filters.search} onChange={...} />
        <StatusFilter value={filters.status} onChange={...}
          options={["all", "PENDING_APPROVAL", "ACCEPTED", "REJECTED", "BLOCKED"]} />
      </div>

      {/* Data Table */}
      <DataTable
        columns={userColumns}
        data={data?.items || []}
        isLoading={isLoading}
        pagination={...}
        actions={{
          onApprove: (id) => updateStatus.mutate({ id, status: "ACCEPTED" }),
          onReject: (id) => updateStatus.mutate({ id, status: "REJECTED" }),
          onBlock: (id) => updateStatus.mutate({ id, status: "BLOCKED" }),
        }}
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

---

### 2.9 Best Practices for Scalability

1. **Module-based architecture** — Each feature is self-contained with `api.ts`, `hooks.ts`, `types.ts`, and `columns.tsx`
2. **Centralized API client** — Single Axios instance with interceptors for auth, refresh, and error handling
3. **React Query for server state** — Automatic caching, background refetch, optimistic updates
4. **Zustand for client state** — Lightweight, no boilerplate, perfect for auth & UI state
5. **Type-safe end-to-end** — Shared TypeScript interfaces from mobile ↔ admin panel
6. **Reusable DataTable** — Single table component handles pagination, sorting, filtering, actions
7. **Protected + Role-based routing** — Clean route guards composable as wrapper components
8. **Consistent theming** — Colors and typography directly extracted from mobile app
9. **Code splitting** — React.lazy() for page-level components, reducing initial bundle
10. **Environment config** — `.env` files for API URLs, no hardcoded endpoints
11. **Error boundaries** — Global error handling matching mobile's `ErrorBoundary` pattern
12. **Toast notifications** — Consistent feedback for CRUD operations via Sonner

---

### 2.10 Mobile ↔ Admin Panel Consistency Map

| Mobile Feature | Admin Equivalent |
|---|---|
| Home featured listings | Dashboard → Featured Listings section |
| Live auctions bidding | Auctions → Monitor bids, extend/end auctions |
| Buy Now purchase | Listings → Manage buy-now prices and availability |
| My Deals | Deals → View all deals across all users |
| Profile edit | Users → Edit any user's profile, change status |
| Sell Vehicle form | Sell Requests → Review and approve/reject |
| Subscription modal | Subscriptions → Manage plans and user subscriptions |
| User status flow | Users → Approve/Reject/Block with status badges |
| OTP verification | Users → View verification status per user |
| Category chips | Categories → Full CRUD for categories |
| Color palette | Theme → Same `#3D5BD9` primary, `#1C2B4A` navy, Urbanist font |
